'''Ryan Donnelly''' (born 23 October 1991) is a Scottish [[association football|footballer]], who plays for [[Gartcairn Juniors]] in the [[Scottish Junior Football Association, West Region]]. He first played for [[Airdrieonians F.C.|Airdrie United]] and has also played for [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]], [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]] and [[Ayr United F.C.|Ayr United]].

==Career==
Donnelly began his career at [[Airdrieonians F.C.|Airdrie United]] initially in the youth team, then signing professionally for the 2010–11 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=RYAN DONNELLY INTERVIEW|url=http://airdriefc.com/news/2011/1111/ryandonnellyinterview.html|publisher=Airdrieonians F.C.|date=13 November 2011|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> His form at Airdrie began to attract interest from other clubs and he was linked with a move to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Celtic eye Ryan Donnelly for the future|url=http://www.express.co.uk/sport/football/295037/Celtic-eye-Ryan-Donnelly-for-the-future|publisher=Scottish Daily Express|last=Esson|first=Blair|date=12 January 2012|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> although he said his preference would be a move to England.<ref>{{cite web|title=I'd choose England over signing for boyhood heroes Celtic, says Scotland's top scorer Ryan Donnelly|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/id-choose-england-over-signing-1113582|publisher=Daily Record|last=McDermott|first=Scott|date=12 January 2012|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> In March 2012, he spent a week training with [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Wigan Athletic trial inspires Ryan Donnelly|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/local-sport/wigan-athletic-trial-inspires-ryan-2826734|publisher=Airdrie & Coatbridge Advertiser|last=Paterson|first=Colin|date=30 May 2012|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> whose Manager [[Roberto Martinez]] said he would continue to keep an eye on him.<ref>{{cite web|title=Donnelly still on Latics radar|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11682/7598370/Donnelly-still-on-Latics-radar|publisher=Sky Sports|date=15 March 2012|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref>

In November 2011, Donnelly won the [[Scottish Football League monthly awards|SFL Young Player of the Month]] award.<ref>{{cite web|title=IRN-BRU SFL November Manager and Player of the Month Awards|url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/irn-bru-sfl-november-manager-and-player-of-the-month-awards/|publisher=Scottish Professional Football League|date=18 December 2011|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> At the end of the [[2011–12 Airdrie United F.C. season|2011–12 season]] he won the [[Scottish Football League|SFL]] Player of the Year award for the [[Scottish Football League Second Division|Second Division]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ross County sweep the boards at SFL end of season awards|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/ross-county-sweep-the-boards-at-sfl-857952|publisher=Daily Record|date=24 May 2012|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> and was named in the [[PFA Scotland Team of the Year#Second Division 2|2011–12 PFA Scotland Second Division Team of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|title=PFA SCOTLAND DIVISION TWO TEAM OF THE YEAR|url=http://pfascotland.co.uk/2012/news/pfa-scotland-division-two-team-of-the-year/|publisher=PFA Scotland|last=Ross|first=Jack|date=3 May 2012|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> In May 2013, Donnelly left Airdrie by mutual consent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Airdrie clearout as eight players leave|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/local-sport/airdrie-clearout-eight-players-leave-2825566|publisher=Airdrie & Coatbridge Advertiser|last=Paterson|first=Colin|date=7 May 2013|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref>

On 21 June 2013, Donnelly signed for [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ryan Donnelly joins The City|url=http://www.brechincity.com/bcfc/servlet/BCFCFrontControllerServlet?action=News&page_id=1340&category=2|publisher=Brechin City F.C.|date=21 June 201|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> He was released by Brechin in January 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ryan Donnelly Released|url=http://www.brechincity.com/bcfc/servlet/BCFCFrontControllerServlet?action=News&page_id=1423&category=2|publisher=Brechin City F.C.|date=10 January 2014|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref>

Donnelly then signed for [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Donnelly is now a Rover|url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/donnelly-is-now-a-rover/|publisher=Scottish Professional Football League|date=10 January 2014|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> He left the club at the end of the 2013–14 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Player Availability|url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/player-availability--ryan-donnelly-26/|publisher=Scottish Professional Football League|date=2 June 2014|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref>

After leaving Albion Rovers, Donnelly spent time on trial with [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dumbarton new boys get off to a flying start at pre-season games|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/local-sport/dumbarton-new-boys-flying-start-3843018|publisher=Hamilton Advertiser|last=Donald|first=Carla|date=11 July 2014|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> On 24 July 2014, he signed for [[Ayr United F.C.|Ayr United]],<ref>{{cite web|title=NEW SIGNINGS|url=http://www.ayrunitedfc.co.uk/new-signings-2/|publisher=Ayr United F.C.|date=24 July 2014|accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref>

Donnelly obtained for his release from Ayr and joined [[Hurlford United F.C.|Hurlford United]] in April 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wilson|first1=Mike|title=Ayr United urged to deliver as relegation scrap enters final furlong|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/ayr-united-urged-deliver-relegation-5493091|accessdate=18 October 2017|work=dailyrecord|date=10 April 2015}}</ref> After a short spell out of the game, he joined his local club, [[Gartcairn Juniors]] in September 2017.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pirie|first1=Mark|title=Ryan Donnelly makes dream Gartcairn debut and vows to battle for promotion|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/local-sport/former-airdrie-albion-rovers-striker-11213202|accessdate=18 October 2017|work=dailyrecord|date=21 September 2017}}</ref>
 
